some of the challenges

00:02:34.830 --> 00:02:38.010
you guys faced when it comes
to how you sell your goods,

00:02:38.010 --> 00:02:41.280
how you sell your games
to users in those markets.

00:02:41.280 --> 00:02:44.130
What were some ideas that you
guys started off with, and then

00:02:44.130 --> 00:02:46.710
what were some solutions
that you went forward with?

00:02:46.710 --> 00:02:48.030
MARK PANELO: Yeah, sure.

00:02:48.030 --> 00:02:52.230
So at Kabam, we pride ourselves
on a really robust live ops

00:02:52.230 --> 00:02:53.760
program and strategy.

00:02:53.760 --> 00:02:57.480
And included in that is a
lot of different strategy

00:02:57.480 --> 00:02:59.850
that we try to implement,
especially with pricing--

00:02:59.850 --> 00:03:03.300
pricing sensitivity
analysis and testing.

00:03:03.300 --> 00:03:06.340
For example, for
India and for Brazil,

00:03:06.340 --> 00:03:09.720
not only do we have our standard
global pricing on our paywall,

00:03:09.720 --> 00:03:11.730
but we actually put low
price entry points--

00:03:11.730 --> 00:03:13.920
IEP entry points--
that's a little bit more

00:03:13.920 --> 00:03:16.420
affordable for those markets.

00:03:16.420 --> 00:03:18.620
We did see an uplift
in the purchase

00:03:18.620 --> 00:03:20.490
velocity for those
lower-priced IEPs,

00:03:20.490 --> 00:03:21.960
but we thought we could do more.

00:03:21.960 --> 00:03:24.210
So we reached out to Google
Play to see whether or not

00:03:24.210 --> 00:03:27.720
they could help us get more best
practice information for India

00:03:27.720 --> 00:03:28.390
and Brazil.

00:03:28.390 --> 00:03:32.690
So we met with Daniel
in the Brazil team,

00:03:32.690 --> 00:03:34.440
and he actually mentioned
that our pricing

00:03:34.440 --> 00:03:38.310
strategy in the Brazil
market is pretty appropriate.

00:03:38.310 --> 00:03:42.210
Then we talked to [INAUDIBLE]
in the Google India team,

00:03:42.210 --> 00:03:46.020
and she mentioned that
we're still a little bit too

00:03:46.020 --> 00:03:47.710
expensive for that region.

00:03:47.710 --> 00:03:53.090
So what we did is, instead of
putting a sub-$1.00 pricing--

00:03:53.090 --> 00:03:55.110
USD pricing
equivalent-- in India,

00:03:55.110 --> 00:03:56.610
we did something a
little bit lower.

00:03:56.610 --> 00:03:59.310
We did a 10 rupee
offer, which equates

00:03:59.310 --> 00:04:02.520
to around like $0.15 USD.

00:04:02.520 --> 00:04:04.020
And while it was
priced really low,

00:04:04.020 --> 00:04:05.580
we did make it up in volume, to.

00:04:05.580 --> 00:04:09.010
So there is no one-size-fits-all
for emerging markets,

00:04:09.010 --> 00:04:11.460
but we just got to test
different price points.

00:04:11.460 --> 00:04:12.627
RAJ AJRAWAT: Yeah, for sure.

00:04:12.627 --> 00:04:14.363
And Jim, with you guys
as well, with some

00:04:14.363 --> 00:04:15.780
of the markets
you're approaching,

00:04:15.780 --> 00:04:17.290
how did you think about that?

00:04:17.290 --> 00:04:18.720
JIM STERN: Yeah, so let's
kind of take a look at it

00:04:18.720 --> 00:04:20.550
from a different
perspective, which is just

00:04:20.550 --> 00:04:23.520
taking a look at what the
cultural and worldwide events

00:04:23.520 --> 00:04:26.380
are that are going on that
you have to be aware of.

00:04:26.380 --> 00:04:29.280
So for example, with
our games in Turkey,

00:04:29.280 --> 00:04:32.920
there is Ramadan and Eid,
which is very important.

00:04:32.920 --> 00:04:35.880
And so we want to
make sure that--

00:04:35.880 --> 00:04:37.980
we want to encourage the
gameplay during that time

00:04:37.980 --> 00:04:38.480
period.

00:04:38.480 --> 00:04:41.110
So we'll put special sales
on during that time period,

00:04:41.110 --> 00:04:43.722
but won't run any
special UA campaigns

00:04:43.722 --> 00:04:45.930
because we know we won't
that get that kind of return

00:04:45.930 --> 00:04:48.040
during that time period.

00:04:48.040 --> 00:04:51.280
And then other
things like VAT tax--

00:04:51.280 --> 00:04:53.550
at the beginning of
the year, we started

00:04:53.550 --> 00:04:58.150
charging VAT on top of all
of the packages that we had.

00:04:58.150 --> 00:05:00.600
And we had to be really aware
of what the impact of that

00:05:00.600 --> 00:05:03.830
was going to be on the players,
especially on the lower

00:05:03.830 --> 00:05:05.580
end, the entry points.

00:05:05.580 --> 00:05:07.850
Because on the
Google side at least,

00:05:07.850 --> 00:05:09.810
there's no pricing
tiers so we can actually

00:05:09.810 --> 00:05:11.425
set up whatever we need to.

00:05:11.425 --> 00:05:12.800
And on the Apple
side, there are.

00:05:12.800 --> 00:05:16.815
So we have to figure
out what kinds of items

00:05:16.815 --> 00:05:18.940
we want to put in there
that will entice them more,

00:05:18.940 --> 00:05:21.210
or how we even pop
up those messages

00:05:21.210 --> 00:05:24.210
to get some of those
early players on board.

00:05:24.210 --> 00:05:27.020
And then I'd say finally,
one other global perspective

00:05:27.020 --> 00:05:30.100
is, do you even take a
look at the local currency.

00:05:30.100 --> 00:05:32.850
So in the case of Turkey,
where we've got a big presence,

00:05:32.850 --> 00:05:36.610
over this last year, there's
been a huge devaluation

00:05:36.610 --> 00:05:37.350
in the market.

00:05:37.350 --> 00:05:39.100
And what you need to
take a look at there,

00:05:39.100 --> 00:05:41.622
then, is how do you
make sure that you're

00:05:41.622 --> 00:05:43.330
being sensitive to
what's going on there.

00:05:43.330 --> 00:05:45.240
Do you put on sales?

00:05:45.240 --> 00:05:48.400
Do you actually reprice what
you're doing at that time?

00:05:48.400 --> 00:05:50.800
Or do you try to come up
with alternative packages

00:05:50.800 --> 00:05:53.620
like rewarded videos,
where they don't

00:05:53.620 --> 00:05:55.270
have to spend as
much during the time

00:05:55.270 --> 00:05:59.950
where the lira's a lot
lower, and really make sure

00:05:59.950 --> 00:06:02.110
that they're able to
still continue to play.

00:06:02.110 --> 00:06:03.250
RAJ AJRAWAT: So I want
to actually follow up

00:06:03.250 --> 00:06:03.820
on that, too.

00:06:03.820 --> 00:06:05.140
So this is interesting.

00:06:05.140 --> 00:06:07.935
You're having to think about,
like, geopolitical issues that

00:06:07.935 --> 00:06:10.060
are happening around the
world to understand, like,

00:06:10.060 --> 00:06:12.100
currency devaluation.

00:06:12.100 --> 00:06:15.130
What did you guys decide
to do in that moment?

00:06:15.130 --> 00:06:17.050
Did you move with
rewarded video?

00:06:17.050 --> 00:06:18.730
Did you change the pricing?

00:06:18.730 --> 00:06:20.530
How did you actually
react to that?

00:06:20.530 --> 00:06:22.258
JIM STERN: No, so
what we figured was

00:06:22.258 --> 00:06:23.800
it was really
important to watch what

00:06:23.800 --> 00:06:25.060
was going on in the market.

00:06:25.060 --> 00:06:27.130
And because these are
lower price point entry,

00:06:27.130 --> 00:06:30.160
it doesn't really impact that
part of the business as much.

00:06:30.160 --> 00:06:32.600
So we decided to wait and
see what would happen.

00:06:32.600 --> 00:06:35.050
And things actually
turned out fine in terms

00:06:35.050 --> 00:06:36.950
of what players
were interested in

00:06:36.950 --> 00:06:39.987
and being able to
engage in the game.

00:06:39.987 --> 00:06:42.320
And it's the one piece that
I think is really important.

00:06:42.320 --> 00:06:44.110
Don't react quickly,
and don't say,

00:06:44.110 --> 00:06:46.240
OK, I'm going to reprice
everything right away.

00:06:46.240 --> 00:06:49.990
Sit, wait, see what's going
to happen, and make sure

00:06:49.990 --> 00:06:52.307
that you're really listening
to what the players want.

00:06:52.307 --> 00:06:53.390
RAJ AJRAWAT: That's great.

00:06:53.390 --> 00:06:55.630
And Mark, I wanted to
actually touch on something

00:06:55.630 --> 00:06:57.700
