we, Kabam, actually have really
deep roots with UC Berkeley.

00:11:06.183 --> 00:11:08.350
And what we've been doing--
like all of our founders

00:11:08.350 --> 00:11:09.018
came from Cal.

00:11:09.018 --> 00:11:11.310
And what we did with them is
we partnered with the Haas

00:11:11.310 --> 00:11:13.270
Business School to do
a research competition

00:11:13.270 --> 00:11:16.960
to see which markets
outside of the tier 1's

00:11:16.960 --> 00:11:19.240
have the highest
growth potential.

00:11:19.240 --> 00:11:22.130
And there's a bigger
opportunity there.

00:11:22.130 --> 00:11:26.860
So it's no surprise that both
India and Brazil, as well as

00:11:26.860 --> 00:11:30.040
Southeast Asia came
up in the research.

00:11:30.040 --> 00:11:32.328
So right now, we're
actually moving to phase 2.

00:11:32.328 --> 00:11:33.870
And in phase 2,
actually, we're going

00:11:33.870 --> 00:11:36.640
to be partnering with
an university in India

00:11:36.640 --> 00:11:40.240
to go a little bit more deeper
on, not only just the game

00:11:40.240 --> 00:11:42.785
market over there, but also
the game tech and the player

00:11:42.785 --> 00:11:43.762
profile.

00:11:43.762 --> 00:11:45.220
And the reason why
we're doing that

00:11:45.220 --> 00:11:47.860
with the university in India
is because we identify them

00:11:47.860 --> 00:11:50.152
as a growth market and
an emerging market,

00:11:50.152 --> 00:11:51.860
those people who are
on the ground there.

00:11:51.860 --> 00:11:53.290
So that's why we
wanted to do that.

00:11:53.290 --> 00:11:54.310
So that's how we're
kind of learning

00:11:54.310 --> 00:11:56.260
from the folks over
there on, the ground.

00:11:56.260 --> 00:11:57.340
RAJ AJRAWAT: Interesting.

00:11:57.340 --> 00:11:58.180
I don't know if
