00:19:30.360 --> 00:19:32.400
I would just say
A/B test everything.

00:19:32.400 --> 00:19:35.460
I mean, sometimes the biggest
wins and learnings come out

00:19:35.460 --> 00:19:36.750
of trial and error.

00:19:36.750 --> 00:19:41.220
But I guess my more
general takeaway and advice

00:19:41.220 --> 00:19:43.710
I could give is to don't
be afraid to ask for help,

00:19:43.710 --> 00:19:45.850
and leverage your
external resources,

00:19:45.850 --> 00:19:48.570
whether it's Google Play,
or local universities,

00:19:48.570 --> 00:19:50.730
or even your peers
in the industry.

00:19:50.730 --> 00:19:52.290
Chances are you'll
learn something

00:19:52.290 --> 00:19:54.123
about emerging markets
that you didn't know.

00:19:54.123 --> 00:19:55.432
And the advice is free, too.

00:19:55.432 --> 00:19:56.640
RAJ AJRAWAT: Yep, definitely.

